    public static String Bugatti_allmodel_desc[]={"The Bugatti Mistral, also called the Bugatti W16 Mistral, is a mid-engine two-seater sports car manufactured in Molsheim, France, by French automobile manufacturer Bugatti Automobiles S.A.S. It was revealed on 19 August 2022. The Mistral is marketed as the fastest roadster in the world. Deliveries to customers will begin in early 2024. All 99 units were pre-sold at a price of 5 million euros.The MISTRAL is a one-of-a-kind wind that heralds the new seasons in southern France, stirring awe in all who experience it. The W16 MISTRAL embodies this and the spirit of BUGATTI, offering freedom, elegance, and speed with the incredible power of the iconic W16 engine. Become one with the element. The most intense roofless experience courtesy of the W16 power. With only 99 units produced, never to be replicated, one thing is clear: youre witnessing automotive history being made.\n\nLAST OF ITS KIND\nThe last road-going model to be produced with the supreme power of the 1600 PS W16 Quad-Turbo, the W16 MISTRAL delivers dizzying high speeds in a body built for winding across scenic vistas.\n\nX-THEME\n" +
            "The X-shaped LED taillights are not only for show. Striking, yet functional, this feature improves the cooling circuit of the mighty W16 Four vertical led headlights add a refined elegance to the superb looks of the roadster. Additionally, their three-dimensional surface helps to boost performance by reducing aerodynamic drag and evacuating the air from the wheel well.\n\n AMPLIFYING ENGINE SOUNDS\n" +
            "The dual engine air scoops amplify the W16s unique sound. These roof-mounted intakes pay homage to the MISTRALs predecessors: the 1934 TYPE 57 ROADSTER GRAND RAID and the first modern-era open-top BUGATTI, the VEYRON 16.4 GRAND SPORT."

            ,"Bugatti has revealed this ornate one-off Chiron Super Sport ahead of Monterey Car Week called the \"Golden Era.\"\n" +
            "The Golden Era is a celebration of Bugatti's greatest hits as the company winds down production of the W-16 engine and transitions to an electrified future under new parent company Rimac.\n" +
            "Hand-drawn sketches of legendary Bugattis cover the car's sides; they took more than 400 hours to produce.\n" +
            "Its become a clich to call a sleek supercar a \"work of art,\" but in the case of the Bugatti Chiron Super Sport \"Golden Era,\" that title is particularly apt. This exquisite machine has been revealed ahead of its official in-person debut at the upcoming Monterey Car Week, sporting beautiful murals on the car's flanks that celebrate Bugatti's heritage.\nWhile the W-16 that has been Bugatti's hallmark only arrived in 2005 with the record-breaking Veyron, the customer wanted his masterpiece to feature important vehicles from throughout the brands 100-plus-year history. The images emerge on the front fenders and doors as the paint fades from the metallic Nocturne Black color to a light golden hue called Dor that is unique to this vehicle. On the passenger side, the 26 hand-drawn sketches include iconic cars like the Type 41 Royale and Type 57 SC Atlantic. There are also depictions of planes, a train, the company's chateau headquarters in Molsheim, and signatures from Jean and Ettore Bugatti."


            ,"The Bugatti Bolide is a track-only sportscar developed by Bugatti Engineering GmbH in Wolfsburg, Germany and manufactured in Molsheim, by French automobile manufacturer Bugatti Automobiles S.A.S., revealed online on October 28, 2020.\nThe main influence on the Bolide's light curb weight is due to the monocoque and all of its components constructed with titanium, along with nearly all of the body panels constructed in carbon fiber. Donning the aggressive design language of an LMP1 racecar (specifically the Bugatti Vision Gran Turismo concept, which preceded the Bolide), including the signature X-shape (itself inspired by the Bell X-1 aircraft), the aerodynamics of the Bolide help it generate more than 2,630 kg (5,800 lb) of downforce at 320 km/h (200 mph), with 1,810 kg (4,000 lb) at the rear wing and another 820 kg (1,800 lb) at the front wing. Additionally, the air scoop of the Bolide is home to a group of dimples, similar to what one finds in a golf ball, that raise up at high speeds, smoothing the laminar flow of air and reducing the aerodynamic drag of the scoop by 10% and a reduction in lift forces by 17%, according to Bugatti. The height of the Bolide, 100 cm (39.2 in), matches the height of the famous Bugatti Le Mans racecar."

            ,"The Bugatti Divo is a mid-engine track-focused sports car developed and manufactured by Bugatti Automobiles S.A.S. The car is named after French racing driver Albert Divo, who raced for Bugatti in the 1920s winning the Targa Florio race twice. It was revealed on 24 August 2018 at The Quail  A Motorsports Gathering in California, United States.The car takes inspiration from the Bugatti Type 57SC Atlantic along with the Bugatti Vision Gran Turismo concept in terms of design and has track performance as its main focus. The car includes a redesigned exhaust system featuring quad exhaust pipes, a 1.8 metre wide fixed rear wing (23% wider than the retractable wing on the Chiron), a NACA duct on the roof that channels air to the rear of the car on a central fin and ultimately on the rear wing for improved downforce, a large front chin spoiler, more refined side skirts, larger air intakes on the front, new head lamps and tail lamps, a vent in the bonnet for improved radiator cooling and vents on the front wheel arches to cool the brakes.\n" +
            "\n" +
            "The interior in the Divo is relatively similar to the more luxurious Chiron, but has Alcantara upholstery and carbon-fibre trim in order to save weight."

            ,"Manny Khoshbin, a collector of exceptionally tasteful cars, just took delivery of this one-of-one Herms Edition Bugatti Chiron bringing together the celebrated French luxury-goods designer and luxury-car specialist.\n" +
            "The limited-edition Chiron is dipped in Herms Craie off white paint and has specially designed cashmere fabric on the door panels, one-of-one badges all around, and a special front horseshoe grille.\n" +
            "Khoshbin started collaborating with the two French brands in 2016.\n" +
            "California-based collector Manny Khoshbin has one of the most exclusive car collections in the United States. When Bugatti announced the Chiron, the 1500-hp replacement to the Veyron, in 2015, Khoshbin knew he wanted something more unique. To explain what \"unique\" means to this collector, he says he was recently offered the Chiron Super Sport 300+, but that wasn't exclusive enough. So, because of his passion for both the French luxury fashion brand Herms and hyper-exclusive Bugattis, Khoshbin collaborated with the two French companies to build a one-of-one Herms Edition Bugatti Chiron."

            ,"Bugatti customers appreciate the exceptional. With the recently completed Divo1 Lady Bug, the French luxury brand has once again demonstrated its high level of expertise in outstanding bespoke application and hand craftsmanship. In the timeframe of around two years, a very special Divo was created in close collaboration with one Bugatti customer, tailored with a one-of-a-kind custom paint scheme among other truly unique features. The Lady Bug was an exceptional challenge and at the same time an unforgettable experience. Due to the nature of the project, where a 2D graphic was applied to a 3D sculpture, and after numerous failed ideas and attempts to apply the diamonds, we were close to giving up and saying: We cannot meet the customers request, explains Jrg Grumer, Head of Color & Trim at Bugatti Design. However, it is our profound conviction that we should never give up and that our foremost motivation should always be to make the impossible possible for the customer. We are proud of the expertise we applied in creating this Divo: a high quality and complex product based on pure craftsmanship and outstanding teamwork between design and development."

            ,"Bugatti set the benchmark even higher with the plan of turning the supercar into a luxury road car suitable for everyday use. The development of the Veyron was one of the greatest technological challenges ever known in the automotive industry.\n" +
            "\n" +
            "Barely any parts, components or systems could be taken from existing car concepts and used in the Veyron. Everything had to be developed from scratch in order to achieve the performance specs and then everything had to be implemented in the car. The process also drew on the experiences of other industries in which materials and systems are routinely subject to extreme speeds and forces, such as aviation and space travel. The Veyron is the first  and the only  supercar to be developed and constructed with a series configuration that can master any driving scenario at any time. Even more than 15 years after its launch, the supercar is still setting benchmarks and inspiring emotion and enthusiasm across the globe.\n" +
            "\n" +
            "The Veyron 16.4 is completely sold out."

            ,"The Bugatti La Voiture Noire, a true marvel of automotive engineering and design, epitomizes beauty in its most extravagant form. From the sleek, aerodynamic contours that seamlessly flow across its body to the meticulously crafted details that adorn its every inch, this exceptional hypercar is a symphony of elegance and power. The exterior, draped in a bespoke black carbon fiber shell, not only enhances the car's performance with lightweight precision but also adds an air of mystique and sophistication.\n" +
            "\n" +
            "The distinctive horseshoe grille, a signature Bugatti element, takes center stage, flanked by intricately designed LED headlights that pierce through the darkness like precision-cut diamonds. The Bugatti La Voiture Noire's silhouette is a harmonious blend of aggression and grace, with muscular lines accentuating its power and a roofline that gracefully slopes towards the rear, creating a sense of perpetual motion even at a standstill.\n" +
            "\n" +
            "Step inside, and the cabin envelops occupants in opulent luxury. Premium materials such as fine leather, brushed aluminum, and carbon fiber adorn every surface, meticulously crafted to the highest standards. The cockpit, a marriage of cutting-edge technology and artisanal craftsmanship, places the driver in the heart of an automotive masterpiece."

            ,"The Bugatti Centodieci (Italian for \"110\") is a limited production mid-engine sports car produced by French automotive manufacturer Bugatti. The car is a homage to the Bugatti EB 110 and a celebration of the Bugatti marque's 110th birthday. It was revealed on 16 August 2019 at \"The Quail  A Motorsports Gathering\" in California, United States. ased on the Chiron, the car takes design cues from the EB 110 such as the five round air intakes which resemble a diamond and the wedge shaped design language. A small horse shoe radiator grille present below the headlamps further harks back to the EB 110. Narrow headlights with LED daytime running function and sharp grooves are used to create an aggressive appearance. The rear consists of eight tail lights along with matt-black quad exhaust pipes placed on either side of a large diffuser, complete with an underbody spoiler and a fixed overhanging rear wing. Due to the use of computer assisted 3D design techniques and the use of Virtual Reality technology, the design team was able to complete the design of the Centodieci in six months."

            ,"One of the most bizarre, elusive and expensive of cars is the Bugatti Type 57SC Atlantic. With its low stance, powerful engine, lightweight construction, 123 mph (200 kph) top speed and influential teardrop body, many believe this is the ultimate Bugatti and the first supercar ever made. Ettores son, Jean Bugatti, who played a large role in the development of the Type 57 series, personally styled the Atlantic. Jeans lines draw an interesting mix of aircraft style together with the avant-garde tear-drop shape. Design highlights include a heavily raked windscreen, riveted fins and kidney-shaped doors with matching side windows. The 75 year history of each Bugatti Atlantic is entertaining conjecture for any Bugatti enthusiast. The first prototype is gone and only two of three aluminum bodied production versions remain largely original."

            ,"The Bugatti Chiron is a mid-engine two-seater sports car designed and developed in Germany by Bugatti Engineering GmbH and manufactured in Molsheim, France, by French automobile manufacturer Bugatti Automobiles S.A.S. The successor to the Bugatti Veyron, the Chiron was first shown at the Geneva Motor Show on 1 March 2016.The car's design was initially previewed with the Bugatti Vision Gran Turismo concept car unveiled at the 2015 Frankfurt Auto Show."

            ,"The Bugatti EB 110 is a mid-engine sports car produced by Bugatti Automobili S.p. A. from 1991 until 1995, when the company was liquidated. A small number of post-production cars were completed afterwards, with the last one built by Dauer in 2002 and another unfinished example completed in 2019. It was the only production model made by Romano Artioli's Italian incarnation of Bugatti. Development of the EB 110 started in 1987 on the engine and chassis, with work being carried out by Tecnostile, headed by Tiziano Benedetti, Achille Bevini, and Oliviero Pedrazzi. The trio had worked on the Lamborghini Miura chassis and engine development and had subsequently established their own company which was known to Ferruccio Lamborghini and Paolo Stanzani who were involved in early talks with Romano Artioli. Stanzani was chosen as company Technical Director thanks to his career experience with the Miura, Espada, and Countach."};

    public static String Bugatti_allmodel_spec[]={"The Bugatti W16 Mistral's engine and its specs need no introduction, but we'll give it one anyway. Dating back to the record-breaking Veyron, the 8.0-liter quad-turbocharged W16 found in the Mistral comes from the Chiron Super Sport 300+. In this incarnation, it produces 1,578 hp. Bugatti has not yet published acceleration or top speed claims, but considering that its last roadster - the Veyron 16.4 Grand Sport Vitesse - reached 254.04 mph and made \"only\" 1,183 hp, the Mistral should easily get closer to 300 mph. We estimate a 0-60 mph time of around 2.4 seconds.\n" +
            "\n" +
            "With 70,000 liters of air being fed through the engine every minute (at full bore) via air intakes behind the headrests, Bugatti says that the W16 Mistral provides an even more engaging connection between the driver and this engine.\n" +
            "\n" +
            "This legendary W16 is paired to a seven-speed dual-clutch automatic transmission, and power is directed to all four corners."

            ,"The Golden Era uses a Bugatti Chiron Super Sport as its base, which packs an 1578-horsepower version of the quad-turbocharged 8.0-liter W-16 and the special long-tailed carbon-fiber bodywork from the 300-mph Super Sport 300+. In our hands, the Super Sport shot to 60 mph in a blistering 2.2 seconds and only needed 14.8 seconds to crest the 200-mph mark."

            ,"The Bolide is built using the framework of the same 8-liter quad-turbo W16 engine and the 7-speed dual-clutch automatic transmission used in the Chiron, although upgrades to the W16 engine allow the Bolide to generate over 1,361 kW (1,825 hp; 1,850 PS) and 1,850 Nm (1,364 lbft) of torque, 183 kW (245 hp; 248 PS), more than the Chiron Super Sport 300+. This increase in power can be attributed to bigger blades in the turbochargers and the different orientation of the turbochargers themselves. Combining the fact that the curb weight of the car is only 1,240 kg (2,733.7 lb), the Bolide can accelerate from 0100 km/h (62 mph) in 2.2 seconds, 0200 km/h (124 mph) in 4.4 seconds, 0299 km/h (186 mph) in 7.4 seconds, 0401 km/h (249 mph) in 12.1 seconds, and 0501 km/h (311 mph) in 20.1 seconds and a top speed projected of more than 501 km/h (311 mph). Additionally, Bugatti states that the Bolide has a 04010 km/h (02490 mph) of 24.62 seconds, and a 05010 km/h (03110 mph) time of 33.62 seconds. According to Bugatti, computer simulations show that the Bolide could lap the Nrburgring in 5 minutes and 23.1 seconds, making it just four seconds slower than the current record holder, the Porsche 919 Hybrid Evo. The Bolide is also simulated to have a lap time at the Circuit de la Sarthe of just 3 minutes and 7.1 seconds, making it 7.6 seconds quicker than the current record holder, the Toyota TS050, which lapped the circuit in 3 minutes and 14.7 seconds."

            ,"The car takes inspiration from the Bugatti Type 57SC Atlantic along with the Bugatti Vision Gran Turismo concept in terms of design and has track performance as its main focus. The car includes a redesigned exhaust system featuring quad exhaust pipes, a 1.8 metre wide fixed rear wing (23% wider than the retractable wing on the Chiron), a NACA duct on the roof that channels air to the rear of the car on a central fin and ultimately on the rear wing for improved downforce, a large front chin spoiler, more refined side skirts, larger air intakes on the front, new head lamps and tail lamps, a vent in the bonnet for improved radiator cooling and vents on the front wheel arches to cool the brakes.\n" +
            "\n" +
            "The interior in the Divo is relatively similar to the more luxurious Chiron, but has Alcantara upholstery and carbon-fibre trim in order to save weight.\n" +
            "\n" +
            "Other notable changes include stiffer springs and dampers, carbon-fibre wiper blades and intercooler shroud, grooved wheel spokes, reduced sound insulation, a lighter sound system and removal of the storage lockers present in the doors and centre console for a weight saving of 35 kg (77 lb) over the Chiron Sport. The engine, a quad-turbocharged W16 unit, is retained from the Chiron along with the 7-speed dual-clutch transmission."

            ,"The Bugatti Chiron Hermes, a magnificent collaboration between two pillars of luxury and performance, is a testament to engineering excellence. At its core lies a formidable powerplantan 8.0-liter quad-turbocharged W16 engine that roars to life with an astonishing 1,479 horsepower and 1,180 lb-ft of torque. This powerhouse of an engine catapults the Chiron Hermes from 0 to 60 mph in a breathtakingly swift time, showcasing its exceptional acceleration capabilities. The meticulous attention to detail extends beyond the powerhouse, with a seven-speed dual-clutch automatic transmission seamlessly channeling this immense power to all four wheels. Embodying the spirit of both Bugatti and Hermes, this collaboration marries unrivaled performance with unparalleled luxury, making the Bugatti Chiron Hermes a rare gem in the world of hypercars, where power and precision converge to create an automotive masterpiece."

            ,"Highly customized, high-powered and exclusive. With the Divo, Bugatti has developed a hyper sports car that revives the luxury car manufacturers coachbuilding tradition. It is powered by Bugatti's iconic 1,500 PS, 8-liter W16 engine, with a top speed restricted to 380 km/h. The Divo is limited to just 40 units in total, each priced at 5 million euros net plus options, and produced in the Atelier in Molsheim. The first deliveries of the hyper sports car were made in August 2020,\n" +
            "and all Divo cars will have been handed over to their owners within the first few months of 2021."
            ,"The Bugatti Veyron, introduced in 2005, was a groundbreaking hypercar that set new standards for automotive performance. Below are the key specifications for the Bugatti Veyron:\n" +
            "\n" +
            "Engine:\n" +
            "\n" +
            "The Bugatti Veyron is powered by an 8.0-liter quad-turbocharged W16 engine.\n" +
            "The engine has a unique configuration with 16 cylinders arranged in a W-shaped layout, effectively four banks of four cylinders.\n" +
            "It features four turbochargers to enhance power delivery.\n" +
            "Power and Performance:\n" +
            "\n" +
            "The Veyron produced a staggering 1,001 horsepower in its original version.\n" +
            "Later versions, such as the Veyron Super Sport, increased the power output to 1,200 horsepower.\n" +
            "The Veyron Super Sport held the title of the world's fastest production car for some time, with a top speed of over 267 mph (431 km/h).\n" +
            "Acceleration from 0 to 60 mph is achieved in around 2.5 to 2.7 seconds, depending on the specific model.\n" +
            "Transmission:\n" +
            "\n" +
            "The Veyron features a seven-speed dual-clutch automatic transmission, providing seamless gear changes.\n" +
            "Special Features:\n" +
            "\n" +
            "To manage the immense power and high-speed capabilities, the Veyron is equipped with advanced aerodynamics, including a deployable rear spoiler for stability.\n" +
            "It has a complex cooling system to manage the heat generated by the powerful engine.\n" +
            "The Veyron's interior is luxurious, featuring high-quality materials and advanced infotainment.\n" +
            "It's worth noting that the Bugatti Veyron represented a significant leap forward in terms of automotive engineering and performance when it was first introduced, and it remains an iconic and highly sought-after hypercar. Keep in mind that my knowledge is based on information available up until January 2022, and there may have been further developments or new Bugatti models introduced since then."
            ,"The Bugatti La Voiture Noire, a pinnacle of automotive luxury and performance, is propelled by an extraordinary powertrain. Nestled under its sleek carbon fiber exterior is a quad-turbocharged 8.0-liter W16 engine, a mechanical marvel that unleashes a staggering 1,479 horsepower and 1,180 lb-ft of torque. This powerhouse of an engine is coupled with a sophisticated seven-speed dual-clutch automatic transmission, enabling seamless gear changes and optimal power delivery. The La Voiture Noire accelerates from 0 to 60 mph in a breathtakingly swift time, showcasing its exceptional performance capabilities. While precise details may vary, the hypercar's top speed is reported to be well above 260 mph, solidifying its status as one of the fastest and most exclusive production cars in the world. Beyond its raw speed, the La Voiture Noire seamlessly blends cutting-edge engineering with bespoke luxury, making it a rare and coveted masterpiece in the realm of hypercars."
            ,"The Bugatti Centodieci, a masterpiece in automotive engineering and design, pays homage to the iconic Bugatti EB110 while pushing the boundaries of performance. Beneath its striking exterior lies a mighty 8.0-liter quad-turbocharged W16 engine, unleashing a remarkable 1,600 horsepower. This powerhouse enables the Centodieci to achieve astonishing acceleration, reaching 0 to 60 mph in around 2.4 seconds. The hypercar's top speed exceeds 236 mph, showcasing its prowess on both straightaways and winding roads."
            ,"The Bugatti Type 57 Atlantic Coup, an automotive icon celebrated for its timeless design and historical significance, is powered by a sophisticated engine that reflects the engineering prowess of its era. Introduced in the late 1930s, the Type 57 Atlantic is equipped with a 3.3-liter inline-eight engine. This advanced powerplant featured a dual-overhead-camshaft design, a rarity during that period, and boasted an innovative dry-sump lubrication system. The engine produced around 200 horsepower, a considerable output for its time, contributing to the Atlantic's reputation as a high-performance luxury car. The Type 57 Atlantic Coup's elegant and aerodynamic design, combined with its advanced engineering, makes it one of the most revered and coveted classic cars in automotive history."
            ,"The Bugatti Chiron Super Sport, a pinnacle of modern hypercar engineering, boasts an impressive combination of power and performance. Underneath its sleek exterior lies an 8.0-liter quad-turbocharged W16 engine, a technological marvel that generates a jaw-dropping 1,577 horsepower. This immense power is harnessed by a seven-speed dual-clutch automatic transmission, enabling lightning-fast gear changes and seamless power delivery to all four wheels.\n" +
            "\n" +
            "The Chiron Super Sport accelerates from 0 to 60 mph in approximately 2.3 seconds, showcasing its extraordinary acceleration capabilities. With a top speed that exceeds 300 mph, the Chiron Super Sport has set records for being one of the fastest production cars in the world. The hypercar's aerodynamics, including an extended rear end and optimized bodywork, contribute to stability at high speeds.\n" +
            "\n" +
            "Crafted for exclusivity and performance, the Bugatti Chiron Super Sport exemplifies the brand's commitment to pushing the boundaries of what's possible in the realm of hypercars, making it a symbol of automotive excellence and a marvel of modern engineering."
            ,"The Bugatti EB110, a groundbreaking supercar from the early 1990s, was a marvel of engineering and performance in its time. It was powered by a 3.5-liter quad-turbocharged V12 engine positioned in a mid-engine layout. The engine, featuring five valves per cylinder, was capable of producing around 553 horsepower and 450 lb-ft of torque.\n" +
            "\n" +
            "The EB110's performance figures were exceptional for its era. It could accelerate from 0 to 60 mph in approximately 3.2 seconds and had a top speed of about 213 mph (343 km/h). These figures showcased the EB110's prowess and contributed to its reputation as one of the fastest production cars of its time.\n" +
            "\n" +
            "The chassis of the Bugatti EB110 featured advanced technologies, including an all-wheel-drive system, which was a rare feature for supercars during that period. The EB110 also had a lightweight carbon fiber and aluminum chassis, contributing to its performance-oriented design.\n" +
            "\n" +
            "Despite its short production run and limited availability, the Bugatti EB110 remains a significant part of automotive history, known for its innovative engineering, impressive performance, and distinctive design."};


