    public static String SSC_allmodel_desc[] = {
            "The SSC Tuatara /tutr/ is a sports car designed, developed and manufactured by American automobile manufacturer SSC North America (formerly Shelby SuperCars Inc.). The car is the successor to the Ultimate Aero and is the result of a design collaboration between Jason Castriota and SSC. Initially powered by a 6.9-liter twin-turbocharged V8 engine, the capacity of the engine was later reduced to 5.9 L (360.8 cu in) in order to allow the engine to have a higher redline of 8,800 rpm.[1] SSC had stated that the power output would be rated at 1,350 hp (1,000 kW) or 1,750 hp (1,300 kW) on E85 fuel, along with a 300 mph (483 km/h)+ top speed.",

            "The SSC Ultimate Aero is a mid-engined sports car that was produced by SSC North America (formerly known as Shelby SuperCars) from 2004 until 2013. The SSC Ultimate Aero held the world production car speed record title, according to the Guinness World Records, from 2007 (when it was officially timed at 255 mph, 410 km/h) until the introduction of the Bugatti Veyron Super Sport in 2010. In April 2013, the Guinness World Records temporarily disqualified the Veyron's record time for a period of five days due to concerns about electronic speed limiting changing the function of the car, but after investigation reinstated the Veyron as the record holder.",
    };

    public static String SSC_allmodel_spec[] = {
            "The SSC Tuatara is a hypercar featuring a 5.9-liter twin-turbocharged V8 engine, delivering a remarkable 1750 horsepower and 1735 Nm of torque. It achieves 0 to 60 mph in just 2.5 seconds and has a top speed of 455 km/h. The Tuatara's advanced aerodynamics, lightweight carbon fiber body, and cutting-edge technology make it a benchmark in the hypercar segment. Limited to only 100 units, it combines extraordinary performance with exclusive design, offering an unparalleled driving experience that represents the pinnacle of SSC's engineering prowess.",

            "The SSC Ultimate Aero is a high-performance supercar with a 6.3-liter twin-turbocharged V8 engine, producing 1287 horsepower and 1508 Nm of torque. It accelerates from 0 to 60 mph in 2.8 seconds and boasts a top speed of 412 km/h, making it one of the fastest cars of its time. The Ultimate Aero's aerodynamic design and lightweight construction ensure exceptional handling and speed. With only 24 units produced, it is a rare and highly sought-after supercar that exemplifies SSC's commitment to pushing the limits of automotive performance and engineering excellence."
    };



